entry.title: Refactor AutofillAgent::ShowSuggestionsOptions
entry.content:
Recently a AutofillSuggestTriggerSource was introduced. Ideally, the

trigger source should define all properties of the suggestion. This is

not the case right now, however. When suggestions are triggered in

AutofillAgent, additional properties are controlled via

ShowSuggestionOptions.



This CL removes the ShowSuggestionOptions and instead adds a new

file suggestion_properties. It defines one function for each property

of ShowSuggestionOptions, which computes the value based on the

trigger source. This way, the properties are defined by the trigger

source and collected in a central place for all trigger sources.

entry.title: Simplify AutofillPopupDelegate::DidSelectSuggestion()'s interface
entry.content:
DidSelectSuggestion() is called when a user previews a suggestion. It

currently has three parameters describing the selected suggestion: The

main text value, frontend and backend id.



On the contrary, AutofillPopupDelegate::DidAcceptSuggestion() is called

when a suggestion is clicked/filled. It takes the entire suggestion

object and the accepted suggestion's index as a parameter.



This CL changes DidSelectSuggestion()'s parameters to just the selected

suggestion. From it, all the existing parameters can be derived. This

makes the interface more similar to DidAcceptSuggestion() (index of the

selected suggestion is currently not needed).



The motivation for this refactoring are manual fallbacks, allowing users

to trigger AutofillSuggestions through the context menu. They will

behave slightly differently and this behavior will depend on the

suggestions. By passing the suggestion to DidSelectSuggestion(),

follow-up CLs become simpler. See crrev.com/c/4562174.



Bug: 1446318

selected.

- form_element_was_clicked: If true, the suggestion was triggered by

clicking into a form element (rather than by editing an existing

value, pressing key down, etc). This is used determine whether TTF

or FastCheckout should be shown.

In the code, they are used mutally exclusively.



This CL replaces these two parameters by a newly introduced enum

AutofillSuggestionTriggerSource, consisting of the following values:

- kFormControlElementClicked

- kTextFieldDidChange

- kTextFieldDidReceiveKeyDown

- kOpenTextDataListChooser

These correspond to all existing ways to trigger Autofill suggestions.

The first one maps to form_element_was_clicked, while the third one

maps to autoselect_first_suggestion.



This simplifes the interface and will make it easier to introduce

new trigger sources (in particular, manual fallsbacks) in the future.



The only interesting changes are in autofill_types.mojom (definition of

the enum), autofill_agent.cc (triggering suggestions from the different

sources) and browser_autofill_manager.cc (using the source to replace

the existing parameters).



All existing call-sites that passed autoselect_first_suggestion = false,

form_element_was_clicked = false are migrated to kTextFieldDidChange.

This corresponds to the existing behavior (even though it seems

semantically weird in a few places).

entry.title: Bundle the origin that sets COOP with the policy
entry.content:
To make the `Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: restrict-properties` (COOP:RP)

more useful, we'd like to let cross-origin iframes inherit this policy

from their parent and keep the opener connection between windows that

the iframes open. To make sure new windows are in the correct

BrowsingInstances, we need to keep track of the origin that sets the

policy when running COOP algorithms. See

https://github.com/hemeryar/coi-with-popups/blob/main/docs/cross_origin_iframe_popup.MD

for more explanations.



This CL is the first of two main steps: it bundles the COOP value with

the origin that sets it. This should not change any behavior except making the COOP: SOAP code work more smoothly. In the

second step, we will use this origin for COOP enforcement and let cross-

origin iframes inherit COOP.

entry.title: Wait until TestV4DatabaseFactory is ready
entry.content:
Take 2 on trying to make sure TestV4DatabaseFactory is ready before being used.



Cannot reproduce as it is very rare, will commit possible fixes and see how it

works on the bots. It should not make things worse as worst case will time out

instead of crash with nullptr.



Ideally this while loop should be in v4_test_util, but it cannot use content/public,

all uses are either directly from safe browsing tests, or indirectly through

TestSafeBrowsingDatabaseHelper so once the right fix is found it should be

possible to contain it to SafeBrowsing code.



Even more ideally, TestV4DatabaseFactory::MarkPrefixAsBad should wait until

ready and return a callback when done. This would require changing the callers

and is probably out of scope.
